00:00:02,350 --> 00:00:04,400
Kimbly!

2
00:00:04,770 --> 00:00:05,980
Hey there.

3
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:11,870
Well?

4
00:00:11,870 --> 00:00:14,740
I'm going to take revenge for what you did to Greed-san and my friends!

5
00:00:14,740 --> 00:00:17,410
Kimbly-san, 
what are you doing here?!

6
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:21,540
It shouldn't be that unusual, 
considering I <i>am</i> a State Alchemist, right?

7
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:24,980
You sold us out and returned to the military! You're the worst!

8
00:00:24,980 --> 00:00:28,850
Are you sure you want to let her kill me like this?

9
00:00:30,090 --> 00:00:31,710
Martel-san, please stop!

10
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:35,220
What are you doing?! 
Let go! Let go of me!

11
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:36,760
Are you all right?

12
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:36,760
Please stop!

13
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:38,880
Let go of me already!

14
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:40,770
You should make for some fine fireworks.

15
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,770
Martel-san!

16
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:42,240
Let go of me!

17
00:00:44,770 --> 00:00:48,000
Kimbly-san, what are you doing to that man?!

18
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,270
I am, first and foremost, a soldier.

19
00:00:50,270 --> 00:00:52,860
There's no reason why I should 
bear the blame of some hooligan.

20
00:00:56,570 --> 00:00:57,720
Martel-san!

21
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:12,780
Man cannot obtain anything 
without first sacrificing something.

22
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:17,370
In order to obtain anything, 
something of equal value is required.

23
00:01:17,910 --> 00:01:22,420
That is alchemy's 
Law of Equivalent Exchange.

24
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:28,980
At the time, we believed that 
to be the true way of the world.

25
00:01:36,910 --> 00:01:42,650
Far away, far away, our dreams will never fade

26
00:01:36,910 --> 00:01:42,650
tooku tooku omoi hatenaku

27
